        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 1:09PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 108 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Ennice to Maple
Springs. Movement was southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
North Wilkesboro...
Elkin...
Wilkesboro...
Fairview...
Yadkinville...
Jonesville...
and Sparta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
